THE MAKING OF VEGAN KIMCHI CREAM PASTA & SALAD 

By @plantbased_matters
More inspiration at plantbasedmatters.net 

Do you like kimchi cream pasta?

One of my old-time favorite pasta dishes is kimchi cream pasta! It's made with homemade vegan kimchi and cashew cream. Both Vegan Kimchi and our Cashew Cream recipes are available at plantbasedmatters.net 

To go with the pasta, I also fixed a simple salad made with my Brazil nut parmensan, also available on our blog. Almost everything is pre-cut so when I want to make one, all I have to do is to put them together.

Very satisfying & comforting meal 😋

自家製キムチとカシューナッツのクリームで作る、ヴィーガンキムチクリームパスタです。たまに無性に食べたくなる味です。

付け合わせは、簡単サラダです。材料は玉ねぎ以外はあらかじめ切ってあるので、短時間で出来ます。サラダにはいつも、酸味と塩味の両方を兼ね備えた梅酢を使います。

PIZZA TIME?

Well, not quite yet...

We are always recipe testing and working on multiple different things when time permits, and today, it's more pizza 🍕 

In the past, we made a few pizzas ( and story shared some) with a Japanese element to it, and it definitely was different in a fantastic tasting way 😀

As I mentioned on @mono_koto_matters post yesterday, all recipes will come in due time. Oh man, do we have some exciting recipes coming...stay tuned.

Thanks for watching!

BUCATINI WITH CREAMY ROASTED RED BELL PEPPER & HARISSA SAUCE!

Recipe by: @plantbased_matters 
Recipe link in bio or at plantbasedmatters.net

If you have been following us for a while, you definitely saw this a few times. This is one of our older recipes when we started our blog, and we wanted to share for those who may have missed it! 

We love fusion cuisine, especially when it's a pasta dish! This Bucatini with Creamy Roasted Red Bell Pepper & Harissa Sauce is one of them where Italian meets Middle Eastern. It's rich and hearty but also an elegant dish. This pasta dish is a definite must try! 

Now, back to my concerts 😅🎻🎻

VEGAN JAPANESE POTATO SALAD
[ヴィーガンポテトサラダ]

Recipe by @plantbased_matters
Recipe link in bio or at plantbasedmatters.net 

Have you tried Japanese potato salad? It's a nostalgic dish for any Japanese person. Japanese potato salad = a taste of mom's home cooking.

Typical Japanese potato salad isn't vegan, but my version is 100% vegan and also made with ALL ORGANIC ingredients, including organic vegan mayo, organic Japanese karashi mustard, and organic dulse flakes! The updated recipe & post of my vegan Japanese potato salad is now up on plantbasedmatters.net. You can find more information about the organic ingredients that I use to make my favorite Japanese potato salad!

日本のポテトサラダはを良く作り置きしておきます。ご飯のおかずにもなりますし、夜にちょっと小腹が空いたときにつまんだり。それぞれの家庭の味があるポテトサラダ、うちではツナ缶が入っていました。母の味を基に作ったヴィーガンレシピはDulse Flakesをツナの代わりに入れています。英語レシピはレシピブログにて公開しています。

GREEN TEA SOBA NOODLE SALAD 

By @plantbased_matters 
More inspiration at plantbasedmatters.net 

What did you eat for breakfast?

When I don't crave anything in particular, I often make noodle dishes, even for breakfast🌞

I put together some cold green tea soba dressed with soy sauce based sesame sauce, shredded red cabbage, red onion, ginger, scallion, toasted sesame seeds, wakame, nori, and grilled tofu. It's prepared sort of in an American style 😅

While this is a non-recipe dish, I use my VEGAN MENTSUYU to make the sesame sauce. It's very versatile, and you can use it as a flavored soy sauce to pour over or to cook with👌

If you'd like to check out the recipe for the VEGAN MENTSUYU, go on plantbasedmatters.net

THE MAKING OF SHIO MUSUBI (SALTED ONIGIRI)
 塩むすび

By @plantbased_matters 
More inspiration at plantbasedmatters.net 

Do you like Onigiri? 

Shio musubi is the simplest but one of the best ways to enjoy onigiri (Japanese rice balls) 🍙

It's just rice, sea salt, and nori seaweed. I use Japanese koshihikari rice, arajio sea salt, and toasted nori seaweed, which you can find them all from @the_rice_factory_ny

I have other onigiri recipes such as miso grilled onigiri ochazuke on our blog at  plantbasedmatters.net 👩‍💻

THE MAKING OF CUCUMBER NUKAZUKE (JAPANESE FERMENTED PICKLES) [きゅうりのぬか漬け]
Have you tried making Nukazuke pickles?

Recipe by @plantbased_matters
Link in bio or at plantbasedmatters.net 

Nukazuke is traditional Japanese pickles in a fermented rice bran bed called nukadoko 👩‍🏫

This unique method of pickling gives a pleasantly briny and umami rich taste to the pickles. Once you make the nukadoko, you simply massage the vegetable of your choice with sea salt and let it nest in the nukadoko for a day or longer if you wish. Wash off the rice bran, slice, and serve with rice! 🥒🍚🥢

Best of all, you can use the nukadoko semi-permanently with proper maintenance!

Both Nukazuke and Nukadoko recipes are available on plantbasedmatters.net 💁‍♀️

VEGAN KIMCHI MISO RAMEN 
[ヴィーガンキムチ味噌ラーメン]

Recipe by @plantbased_matters
Recipe link in bio or at plantbasedmatters.net 

Do you like ramen and kimchi?

Ramen has always been my favorite comfort of all 🍜🤤 If you're like me, try making Vegan Kimchi Miso Ramen at home!!

It's easy to make and super delicious. The savory miso broth is rich, spicy, garlicky, and slightly tangy with a hint of sweetness. It's got a great aroma from toasted sesame oil.

I use my homemade vegan kimchi along with gochujang and authentic Japanese miso. The result is one tasty, complex, and umami-rich broth.

I recommend using good napa cabbage kimchi, Japanese miso, and chewy ramen noodles of your choice 👩‍🍳

The recipe is available at plantbasedmatters.net

HIYAYAKKO [冷奴] 

By @plantbased_matters
More inspiration at plantbasedmatters.net 

Hiyayakko is a chilled tofu, a Japanese side dish. 

There are many different ways & variations to enjoy hiyayakko. For the tofu, you can use silken (soft) tofu or firm tofu. For the sauce, the variations are endless.

If you want to try this in the most basic way, serve as a cut silken tofu with soy sauce and some condiments such as scallions and grated ginger.

On this particular day, I used firm tofu with the sauce made of smoked soy sauce, rice vinegar, toasted sesame oil, toasted sesame seeds, and tobanjang.

Have you tried this before?

WASABI (JAPANESE HORSERADISH)
New Vegan Japanese Pantry Guide 👩‍🏫

By @plantbased_matters

Do you like Wasabi? The distinctive "wasabi effect" is something that no other spicy condiments would give. The sharp sensation that goes through the back of your nose and getting teary-eyed is quite an experience 😂

While grating a real wasabi root would be the best, in most cases, we use the alternative such as a paste or power.

Whatever you may find, check to see if it's "real" or "genuine" wasabi...yes, some wasabi may not even have any wasabi in it!!🤯

Read more about Wasabi on plantbasedmatters.net 👩‍💻

Recipe link in bio or at plantbasedmatters.net

I have to say, it was still as good as when I first posted the recipe a few years ago 😋 It's super easy & tasty even for those who aren't really familiar with this type of noodle dish. 

You could make this recipe with what you probably have in your pantry + fridge. What's more comforting than a bowl of creamy noodles?☺ 🥢

JAPANESE SWEETS ANYONE?

Toasted "oyaki" with anko filling (sweet adzuki bean paste). Oyaki is a Japanese savory or sweet dumpling with fillings.

It's warm and crunchy on the outside and the anko filling has a perfect amount of sweetness which isn't overly sweet, the Japanese way 😋 This fantastic oyaki is made by the Japanese lady, Arai-san, from @sankyodainatto Highly recommended 👌

This warm, hearty, and easy-to-make vegan Somen Noodles in Creamy Sesame Miso Soup is one of the popular recipes on our blog!🍜

THE MAKING OF CREAMY MISO NAPA CABBAGE PASTA 
[白菜のクリーミィ味噌パスタ]

By @plantbased_matters
More inspiration at plantbasedmatters.net 

Recipe down below 👇

Our brunch today is pasta 😋
I just whipped up some Japanese inspired pasta on the whim. The interesting ingredient here is the "onion shio koji" which is a variation of "shio koji" but made with onion so it gives that onion punch 🧅👊 You could substitute with shio koji or skip it all (although it may change the overall flavor.) If interested, our shio koji recipe is available at plantbasedmatters.net 

Here is the quick recipe 👩‍🍳👇

1️⃣Start boiling spaghetti of your choice.

2️⃣Sauté garlic & ginger in sesame oil.

3️⃣Add napa cabbage and cook until the white parts are translucent.

4️⃣Add water, sake, onion shio koji, miso, and mix well and add baked tofu.

5️⃣Pour unsweetened  soymilk or any plant-based milk. Mix and let it simmer until thickened and slightly reduced.

6️⃣Once pasta is done, add to the creamy sauce and toss.

7️⃣Serve on a plate and finish with toast sesame oil, scallions, and shichimi pepper.

THE MAKING OF HOME-MADE VEGAN PIZZA 🍕
[おうちピザ]

There's nothing more cozier than staying home and cooking all day. Over the weekend, I decided to make pizza using what we already have. Flour, yeast, sugar, salt, and water for the dough. Passata & our homemade cashew cream as the sauce. You can find our Cashew Cream recipe on our blog at plantbasedmatters.net. I also used Red onion, green bell pepper, and stuffed olive for the toppings.

I've tried the pizza dough recipe from one of Vegan Richa's cookbooks. I had to modify the amount of flour as it somehow became too sticky and unmanageable 😂 Baking is totally not my strength, but it's really rewarding when it comes out right and delicious in the end ✌️

SPICY GARLIC AND OIL PASTA WITH AONORI
[青のりペペロンチーノ]

Food & 📸 by @plantbased_matters
Recipe link in bio or at plantbasedmatters.net

Will you be giving this a try?

Who loves oil-based pasta? I do 🙋‍♀️ This Spicy Garlic and Oil Pasta with Aonori is a Japanese fusion of the Italian dish, spaghetti aglio olio e peperoncino 🍝🌶 The green stuff isn't parsley---it's aonori (dried green seaweed flakes) which makes this dish taste uniquely Japanese.

 The heat is from Japanese takanotsume peppers (hawk claw pepper, ) and it's seasoned with a hint of soy sauce! I also share some useful tips on how to make a perfectly seasoned garlic & oil pasta on this recipe post. Go over to plantbasedmatters.net for the recipe and the tips👩‍💻👩‍🍳

ペペロンチーノも美味しいですけど、青のりペペロンチーノはもっと美味しいです😋 オイルソースはパスタを茹でる際の水と塩の割合を上手く調整して、それをソースに混ぜると、こういうシンプルなパスタも想像以上に美味しくなりますよね。ちなみに、以前にこういう和風パスタを以前にアップしたら、「イタリア料理を侮辱するな」みたいなコメントをイタリア人から頂きました（笑）でも懲りずにまたウェブサイトにて英語レシピ公開しています😜

レモンケイパー風味ちりめんキャベツのサラダ（ヴィーガン）

Food & 📸 by @plantbased_matters

Do you like Yakisoba?

Yakisoba is Japanese stir-fried noodles. It's a simple & quick but delicious noodle dish that you can make by adding a few veggies like cabbage and green bell pepper.

Have you tried making Nukazuke pickles? 

Nukazuke is traditional Japanese pickles fermented in rice bran.

We typically eat nukazuke with rice, but you can make pasta with it, too 😋

I had cucumber and baby eggplant nukazuke already prepared. Simply slice them and combine with chilled capellini and the sauce made of shio-koji, rice vinegar, and olive oil.

Serve with freshly ground black pepper and shiso leaves on top🍃

It's easy to make and super delicious. The savory miso broth is rich, spicy, garlicky, and slightly tangy with a hint of sweetness. It's got a great aroma from toasted sesame oil.

I use my homemade vegan kimchi along with gochujang and authentic Japanese miso. The result is one tasty, complex, and umami-rich broth.

I recommend using good napa cabbage kimchi, Japanese miso, and chewy ramen noodles of your choice 👩‍🍳
